<td colspan="3" style="font-size:85%;"><span class="citation wikicite" id="endnote_aaa"><b><a href="#ref_aaa">^</a></b></span> The DPRK Constitution defines the Chairman of the National Defence Commission as the "supreme leader" of the DPRK.<br />
<span class="citation wikicite" id="endnote_bbb"><b><a href="#ref_bbb">^</a></b></span> Kim Yong-nam is the "<a href="Head_of_State" title="Head of State" class="mw-redirect">head of state</a> for foreign affairs". The position of president (formerly head of state) was written out of the constitution in 1998, and <a href="Kim_Il-sung" title="Kim Il-sung">Kim Il-sung</a> (who died in 1994) was given the appellation <a href="Eternal_President_of_the_Republic" title="Eternal President of the Republic">Eternal President</a> in its preamble.</td>
